Eight people, including two children, died following a collision on the N11 between Ladysmith and Newcastle on Saturday night. JOHANNESBURG – KwaZulu-Natal’s Transport MEC Bheki Ntuli said fatalities on the province's roads could be avoided if motorists obeyed the rules. Eight people, including two children, died following a collision on the N11 between Ladysmith and Newcastle on Saturday night. Ntuli said: “According to the information I have, one of the drivers was over speeding, he lost control and came to the wrong side of the road.”